content:
Using a cache to store frequently accessed, infrequently updated Data Mapper and Integration Procedure data saves round trips to the database and improves performance. Caching of Data Mapper and Integration Procedure metadata and Integration Procedure data is available in Summer '19 and later releases.

If you use OmniStudio, Data Mappers and Integration Procedures use the Scale Cache. If you use OmniStudio for Vlocity, Data Mappers and Integration Procedures use the Platform Cache.

You can cache metadata for the entire Integration Procedure or the response of the entire Integration Procedure. You can also cache the result of a specific set of steps by placing them inside a Cache Block.

To configure top-level caching for an Integration Procedure, go to the Procedure Configuration and set the Salesforce Platform Cache Type and Time To Live In Minutes properties.

Metadata is automatically cached for Data Mappers unless you turn off the Scale Cache. Integration Procedure metadata is cached by default.

You can clear metadata from the cache using methods such as `clearCacheForDataRaptor` or `clearMetadataCache`. You can also clear all cached data for an Integration Procedure, including session cache data, org cache data, and metadata.

To clear Data Mapper data from the Scale Cache, use a line of code in this form: `namespace.ScaleCacheService.invalidateCacheValue(new Map<String, String>{'DataRaptorId' => DataRaptor_Name});`.
title: Caching in OmniStudio for Vlocity
